      Congrats on your dinosaur Ken Griffin
   =20
 =20
I feel like, when you read about someone buying an expensive bauble, maybe =
50% of the time it is Ken Griffin? Pretty much anywhere you go in the world=
, Griffin has bought the most expensive home there. He owns a Constitution.=
 Also now he=E2=80=99s got a dinosaur:Hedge-fund billionaire Kenneth Griffi=
n paid $44.6 million for a nearly complete Stegosaurus skeleton at Sotheby=
=E2=80=99s on Wednesday, the most ever paid for a fossil at auction.The 150=
 million-year-old dinosaur, nicknamed =E2=80=9CApex,=E2=80=9D was only expe=
cted to sell for up to $6 million. Its sale surpassed the $32 million paid =
four years ago by Abu Dhabi for a Tyrannosaurus rex skeleton widely known a=
s =E2=80=9CStan.=E2=80=9D The sale also soared past the $8.4 million paid i=
n 1997 for another T.rex nicknamed =E2=80=9CSue,=E2=80=9D now on view at Ch=
icago=E2=80=99s Field Museum.=C2=A0Griffin, the 55-year-old founder and chi=
ef executive of Citadel, said he aims to lend =E2=80=9CApex=E2=80=9D to a m=
useum in the U.S. =E2=80=9CApex was born in America and is going to stay in=
 America,=E2=80=9D he said after the sale.Good for him. You sometimes read =
stories like =E2=80=9CArea Billionaire Lives Modest Life in Modest House, D=
rives Modest Car, Sometimes Flies Commercial,=E2=80=9D and, you know, why? =
What is the point of all that money if not to spend it on amusing toys? If =
you=E2=80=99ve got a huge collection of huge houses, why not put a stegosau=
rus in the foyer of one of them?=C2=A0Also, I realize that crypto is back, =
but in 2021 Griffin had to bid against a crypto decentralized autonomous or=
ganization to buy that Constitution. There was not, as far as I know, a Ste=
gosaurusDAO in 2024, so crypto isn=E2=80=99t=C2=A0fully=C2=A0back.
